caption: enjoyed the Carnegie asada tacos.

Awesome, clean tacos. They taste fresh, the ingredients taste fresh. It’s a bit pricey, but you won’t be disappointed. I had the pork, chicken, & Carne Asada combo, they all tasted great & I believe the pork one had pineapple, the flavors were just 👌🏽 & the margarita was top tier, 10/10
Absolutely delicious!!! Allows indoor dining because it’s close to the hospitals. Highly recommend!!

Pretty prompt service, good food, cool atmosphere, but only so satisfied by their tacos. Having had legit street tacos from various stands in Mexico, the bar is already set pretty high for me, so no offense, tallboy

This place is a scam you think you're getting a good taco for the price almost $5. Tallboy Taco is something you could make at home. It's called Tallboy Taco seems like you'll get some hearty tacos. The tacos only come with meat and cilantro. This place got the nerve to charge a Covid surcharge on top of their over priced tacos. Once was enough for me never again and don't reccomend eating here
They did a great job at this new location. Looks much better on the inside. Food seems to have improved. I loved it before, like it even more now.

Before this place horchata was nothing to me but cinnamon toast crunch milk. When I took a sip of thiers I legitimately teared up. It was arguably one of the most delicious things I have ever tasted in my 20 years of living on this planet. God bless this place, God bless tacos and God bless america.

Just spent almost $30 for 3 tiny steak street tacos, a quarter cup of guacamole with way too much lime, and a coke.. tacos only come with onions and cilantro.  Was like eating way over priced chipotle but much smaller, and less.add ons/options. Oh can't forget the 4% covid surcharge.  Not worh the money and still hungry,  won't be back.
Yum yum yum! The shrimp tacos all day long. Excellent guac and Mexican Coke round out a tasty meal. The staff was incredibly gracious. Definitely recommend.

I tried Tall Boy Taco for the first time today and all I can say is I WILL BE BACK. I got the nachitos (nachos) and they gave out a free taco for the grand opening of the Streeterville location. Everything was so delicious 😋 I’m so excited to go back.

Food was over an hour late, needed to pick up at a different address but they don’t feel the need to tell people that. Almost gave us someone else’s food. People who came 30 minutes after us getting their food before us.

Very disappointed with the serving size of my $8.50 kale salad and my $3.95 protein portion. I added the highlighter so you could get a sense of the size of the container.   And if you zoom in, you can see that the container is barely filled half way up with lettuce.  I really like you guys food and I know times are hard, but people expect some kind of value for their money.  This was ridiculous!  I was so disappointed I couldn’t eat it.  I just put it in the fridge.  Actually, the only reason you got three stars is because I really loved the crispy fish tacos that I bought with it!!  Hmph...should have stayed with the tacos and I wouldn’t be disappointed, huh?

I loved this place. It used to be my absolute favorite taco spot in Chicago, but I think whomever changed the menus, is really  high on drugs, because its trash now. Unfortunately, I  won't be coming back.

The appetizers are good! Good customer service.  Went during happy hour. Not crowded nice lil environment . The pitchers of Margarita could have been better. You would have to drink a whole one to yourself just to feel a buzz.
Worth a stop for sure. Drinks and tacos were both good.
Expensive for a raci joint. Food is great but portions are small. 2 bits from my taco and I'm done.
Love the beyond chorizo tacos!!  Vegetarian option!   Guacamole amazing as well.

Really Delicious tacos....loved the BBQ pulled pork taco & the shrimp taco.  Absolutely scrumptious.  Freshly fried in-house corn chips served with mildly spiced salsa & creamy delectable guacamole.  Great Margaritas to accompany your exotically flavored "South of the Border" tacos.  Nice ambiance with a comfortable noise level that allows you to converse with your guests. Casual dining & moderately priced, I highly recommend Tallboy Taco.
Have stopped here twice while in the area. Both times the tacos have been awesome! The variety to choose from is nice and the service was very quick.

Had the great pleasure of kicking off Restaurant Week 2020 tonight with Tallboy Taco and the menu is completely refreshed and more exciting than ever. Dinner for 2 is $36 dollars that includes a chips & guac appetizer (or kale salad), 6 eccentric tacos that go from A - Z (we had the spicy thai shrimp, two types of pork, buffalo chicken, korean steak, and the eggplant which is a must). If you like traditional tacos, but also like to mix it up, Tallboy is for you. Tacos were similar to Velvet Taco, but a way better atmosphere for lunch with colleagues or drinks with friends. While we liked the tacos, we loved the service. The best part about eating tacos is those that serve them!

Great tacos at a great price! The corn fundido is amazing, similar to elite but not spicy. We all agreed the chips were magical, and there is a salsa bar where you can pick your own salsas. Our server was nice and super attentive, food came out quickly as well. I had friends get the churro and it looked good, you also have the option of ordering off the Nacional 27 dessert menu. I'll get be back to Tallboy!
I was so excited to eat here, after visiting the website. The tacos are horrible. They were small and cold when they served them. A WASTE OF MONEY. SHOULD NOT BE LOCATED DOWNTOWN
The brisket tacos are a favorite, salsa bar offers a lot of variety.

The Crispy Fish, sitting pretty on a homemade corn tortilla dancing with a marinated pico de gallo and the Brisket with onion tacos were...well...remember when Homer Simpson would hold his head back, drool, and make that aaaagggghhhh sound when he ate good food? Yes...that would describe those two varieties. The Chicken Mole taco tasted like a good tamale your drunk aunt would make.  The Carne Con Papas had very unappetizing pieces of dried potatoes mingled with a funky flavored steak. The Carne Asada shared a very similar funky flavored steak. Our children refused to eat either. No thanks. The Chicken Tinga...was just not our thing. The combination of ingredients were not tasty or exciting. GO so you can drool!
Fish tacos are to die for. Great atmosphere.

Good food, but I gave several issues with my order...  first of all, these are not $4 tacos :-( They taste great, just not much to them, they feel pretty small unwrapping them and after eating 4 tacos and a tortilla soup I’m still hungry.  Also, every taco I ordered was mislabeled so it was a bit of a mystery figuring out what I was eating :-:    Good food, but tightening up a few key details would make my experience a lot more enjoyable.
The brisket tacos are phenomenal
Nice place
Not really authentic Mexican food but I really didn't think it would be beforehand. Portions weren't sufficient & menu limited. Drinks, though very pricey, were decent.
Tasty food and friendly efficient staff! Can't wait to come back for more!

Margaritas taste like premix from Jewel  Update: My original 1 star review was a little unfair as the service was great (though our server accidently spilled water on our table), the food was both a hit and a miss. A couple of the tacos were great, while a couple of our non-taco orders are not on par with what you'd expect from an establishment that specializes in serving Mexican cuisine.
The chips and guacamole were delicious. We got the two tacos and a shorty for dinner and it was well worth it.
Cowboy tacos are a mouthful of flavor.
The food is awesome and so is the staff!!!
Good tacos
Excellent food at Naciobal 27, used a room at Tallboy, chef Corey us great!
yesterday in lolla it good, please put more avocado !!

Ordered carry out for lunch today, and my sister ordered 2 fish tacos, 1 shrimp taco, 1 steak taco, and 1 brisket taco for the two of us, and it reflected as such on the receipt she was given. Except that when we got back to eat, there was only 1 fish taco and no shrimp taco anywhere to be found, and instead we were given two mystery tacos that we think were chicken and pork, but most definitely not the tacos we had asked for. I’m usually understanding about these sorts of mixups, but the place was absolutely empty when we came in, so there was really no excuse for completely butchering two of only five tacos that we ordered. Not to mention we picked the shrimp and fish tacos because they were listed as the “top choices” on the menu, yet for whatever reason the cooks had a very difficult time actually getting them right on an incredibly slow day. Alas, we ate the tacos anyways as we did not feel like walking back to the restaurant, but let me tell you, they were nothing special. I noticed another reviewer compare the guacamole to jewel brand guacamole that comes in a plastic tub, and I’ve gotta say that’s pretty spot on. The ingredients did not taste particularly fresh, and for almost $4/taco, it’s just not worth it. There are far better places to go spend your money for a quality taco that you actually ordered.
Great tacos and guacamole.

Go somewhere else!  There’s a reason this restaurant wasn’t busy on a Saturday night and we should’ve turned around.  The food isn’t made fresh. If I wanted guacamole plastic tub I would’ve gone to Jewel Osco. Whole the menu is fairly inexpensive, but it is not a good value. Getting very mediocre tacos (at best) for nearly $4 a pop.  Food came quickly because the restaurant wasn’t full, but the wait staff was extremely slow.  Definitely trusted the open table reviews for this choice and was let down. So I’ll be the one to say it, do not go you can find somewhere way better!
Tiny soggy tacos and expensive too, only one tortilla per taco ensured everything fell apart. To add insult to injury, the salsa in the to go cup was only 5 percent filled.

A bit pricey, but the tacos are carefully prepared, they tasted very fresh. They're small though, and served on a single tortilla, instead of the standard 2 tortillas all tacos are served in in most taquerías. The number of offerings in the menu is relatively small, but they have some unique tacos, such as the crispy avocado taco. DELICIOUS!! A must-have, I had never had it anywhere else. This is not strictly a taquería because there are some things such as the papas bravas that are kind of out of place, definitely not Mexican, they belong more in a tapas bar menu. This place has a salsa bar, with great, freshly-made salsas and really good pico de gallo. Highly recommended!! Despite their shortcomings, I will be going back.
Delicious tacos.

Literally a rip off. Like yes, these were taco's that they served me, but what they lacked in flavor they overcompensated for in price. $4 for some bland meat in a soggy tortilla was a total waste of money.
Great tacos and the best margarita I have ever had!
I came, I saw, I taco'd.  It's another taco joint
Great spot
Great tacos, but not really Mexican food.

Ordered Caviar takeout. Not only did I pay extra for standard things like cheese and sour cream they didn't get put in. The flan I ordered was maybe 1/2 cup worth of product that was liquid. I ordered 2 combo plates and I know it isn't taco truck status but there was maybe 3/4 of rice that was flavorless like Rice Roni. The tacos...had tomato with the edges peeling up and looked like old salad bar veg. They only put one tortilla per taco. I can't believe I spent 49 dollars on this meal that can barely feed on person. It's so hard to know what is good in travel areas because everything is rated high. Would not recommend.
Good tacos
Best tacos
Really good tacos. I liked both the steak options. I did carry out, but the interior looks fun!
The passion fruit margarita is my favorite
Great tacos (for Chicago)
Great tacos and occasionally have great deals
Forgot meet ordered on my salad, but replaced the entire salad to make up for it
The burrito was delicious and everything was a good price.
Fantastic tacos and chill bar area too.
Stopped here to eat. Reallygood!!!!
Atmosphere is great but their homemade tacos were very stiff and greasy. Margaritas were way too sweet.

Tallboy food was not impressive. Their rice and beans was flavorless. I had their burrito carne asada, it was just okay, but not worth 9.50. My wife said their tacos were okay but not worth the 12.50 for the taco platter.  If you like really good mixed drinks than Tallboy is where you should go. I don't think I would recommend Tallboy to any of my friends looking a good place to get Mexican food.
Tacos were bland and small
Loved it! Loved the music, loved the ambiance, loved the food!
Taste was good but portions are tiny. Pictured is a $4.25 taco. Better off going to Big Wig or Velvet Taco.

I used to come here for lunch nearly every day! I have since moved, but even after a few years, it’s everything I remembered. The tacos are stellar, the chips are amazing, and the agua frescas are too good to pass up. Open only on weekdays for lunch. Best tacos in Chicago, in my opinion.
Super tasty best deal shorty and 2 tacos 8 bucks loved my adorable bartender server

Went for restaurant week and got their promotional menu, it was amazing! Food was spot on, drinks were great, and the service was perfect. We will definitely be back next time we come back to Chicago!!
This restaurant has good tacos, I tried this place during restaurant week and I think I will definitely come back for more once the weather gets better.
Awesome food and drink specials were on point.
Food just ok. Great service & drinks but probably my least favorite LEY restaurant. The ambiance could also use a facelift. Not recommended for pescetarians, vegetarians & vegans.
Very good. Taco are flavorful no need for salsa. The guacamole is a must. Good atmosphere
For street Tacos fun times great guac and an amazing salsa bar.

They have a great deal of two tacos and a small mug of beer for $8. Good variety. Decent tacos. we also ordered the beer queso...great flavor, just a little too runny. Vibe was really good. Nice decor with bicycles hanging off the roof and graffiti styled walls. The back pumped out great music for the folks that showed up for the Friday night scene.

We love this place! We’ve lived within walking distance for 10 months and are LEYE Frequent Diners, so it’s hard to resist Taco Tuesday. Not only are the tacos the best, but Joey is the best and he will always make sure everything you order is completely up to satisfaction. My fiancé and I got engaged last week and he overheard that and gave us a champagne toast! If you’re in the River North area, you MUST visit TALLBOY TACO!!!
Was ok, but I got the impression it may be hit or miss at times, dont know why.

Tacos tested very good, but were very greasy. Great salsa options. Our waiter was slow and actually forgot my drink order once. Not a fan of their chips. They turn into a fun Latin club after closing.

I cannot say that I was particularly impressed. It might even be a stretch to give a full 3 stars, I'd lean towards 2.5 stars.  The portion sizes are meager, the tacos small, the sides too small.  I ordered chips and salsa, 3 tacos, and a side of rice and beans. I left there unsatisfied.  The patio ambiance was bland.  Very tight, the table was wobbly, the service was mediocre at best.  There are too many better taco places in the area to recommend this spot.
Great option for lunch. I don't love their tortilla chips, but some interesting fusion taco flavors. Nice atmosphere. Part of the Lettuce Entertain You group.
High tacos and good
Surprisingly very good tacos and service was good too. I went there on a Friday for after hours it was a good crowd and a lot of fun.
Great tacos, agua fresca, margaritas and mojitos! Definitely recommend.
Bring your own drink if u going over there!

5th and last time here! Yesterday 8.16.18, the service SUCKED! There was no hostess, the bartender told us to seat ourselves and when ready come place our order at the bar. Soon as my mom sits down, she feels water on her shoulder (air conditioner leaking above), we move to another table and now the same thing happens to my daughter. Finally find dry seats, now a young lady comes over and asks for a drink order. Then a different lady comes and asks if we were ordering appetizers. The drinks come out in 1/2 clean glasses, a third person comes to take the food order (and we had to repeat it several times)... The battered fish tacos were soggy and the spicy chicken was NOT! Used to like happy hour here, not anymore!
Absolutely outstanding.  Great flavors, fresh ingredients, wonderful attentive staff. Try the brisket, shrimp or asada tacos.  Great deal with two tacos and a beer.  The guacamole is a winner.
Good good, friendly and fast wait staff.
Low key. Good food and drink. Doesn't try to be more than it is. Great work lunch or happy hour place.
Really good tacos - especially the fish, shrimp, and steak tacos.  Beer was too expensive, though - $4 for a can of Tecate that should cost 75c at the store

Meh.  3/3 tacos were too sweet and not balanced at all lacking acidity and lots of salt. Pork meat was dry. Carne asada wasn't skirt nor grilled, but soft marinated, good but not for a taco. Tortillas were good.

Good tacos!
Delicious tacos! I love the crispy yet flexible texture of the shell. I highly recommend the brisket taco.
Good food, pricy but a solid meal.
Amazing tacos, with a real proper fresh taste. Everything here is amazing.
This place was alot of fun, great staff, good prices on cocktails and tacos

Wow!  These tacos are legit.  I’ve had so much fun at Pa Gozar...even though I don’t know what it means
The service was fantastic. My food was amazing. I am definitely going back.

Decent food. Able to accommodate for a vegetarian. Average price for what you get. Just try to hightail it out before the club in the back opens.

Booze place than food that is a bit unusual for a Lettuce Entertain You family.  $4+ is haute taco, but TALLBOY's taco is in between haute and street.  Therefore, best to enjoy them on a deal, NOT a la carte.  Housemade tortillas is appreciated.  $6 POZOLE is a perfect, single serving, light meal that is packed with flavor and equal amount of ingredients.  SKIP the SHRIMP SCALLOP CEVICHE.  Like the rest of the city's ceviche, it's a bit chewy and overcooked.  Best served, freshly made.  Brown Bag your leftover CHIPS for FREE breakfast-at-home.  Grease seeps through the bag.  But, CHIPS stay crunchy with your at-home chilaquiles.  Darn CHIPS are stinkin' addictive. (+1 star)  HORCHATA was a okay.  Impeccable SERVICE by Eddie, considering that he was doing a one-man show -- bartender, server, and prolly closed the night.

I didn't go here during the day, or even for the purpose of eating there at all. But it's very nice in there. When I was there, I came to dance, and they're music choice (all Latin") is good for that. I'd definitely go name
Delicious tacos and drinks. It was during lunch, and it was bar service. Everything moved quickly and we were satisfied with the service.

This place is wonderful. Nice waitress, nice service, delicious food. I went with my friend there and his favorite tacos is the steak or beef tacos but when I convinced him to try the spicy chicken, omg he went crazy and forgot about the steak we ordered and wanted just to eat the spicy chicken . We had a good moment there 😍
Great spot. One of the best casual places in the neighborhood. Always fast great tacos and drinks
They have great margaritas! They also have excellent food & drink specials. The shrimp tacos are a must try!

(Translated by Google) The place is very nice but in particular I liked the tacos and they brought them with the cold tortilla  (Original) Esta muy bonito el lugar pero en lo particular los tacos mo me gustaron y me los trajeron con la tortilla fría
Good selection of tacos and they salsa bar options are on point. Also they have the impossible taco!

Brought colleagues from out of town for a taco treat on a Tuesday evening - very chill spot with enjoyable Latin vibes. This is the place if you want fresh, authentic ingredients served up. I also highly recommend the chips and salsa bar — lots of varieties to explore.  Also...little known happy hour secret, arrive before 7pm like we did for $2 tacos (all tacos apply) and $5 House-made sangrias. Totally worth it. Oh, and don’t leave without a house-made churro with their chocolate and dulce de leche sauces. Wish I snapped some photos!
Went for their $2 taco Tuesday special.  Sooo good!
Great decor, good tacos but mediocre al pastor.
Very helpful, had wonderful vegan and veggie options so I could feed a crowd.

Decent tacos, bigger than the usual hipster sized ones you get at places like taco joint. I actually didn't have one, I had the spinach salad with avocado and walnuts. I got plenty of salad, not much dressing, but I was good with that. Also had the corn chowder. The taste was fine, amount was fine, but it could have been warmer. The service was good, I like the fact that bring out theas son add its ready, and not wait for the entire table is ready to bring all the food at once. I enjoyed my lunch and will try it again.

The Impossible Taco is AMAZING! Probably one of the best tacos I've ever had and you can't tell that it's not meat at all! It's entirely 100% plant based. Definitely coming back to this place. Best tacos in Chicago by far.
Solid 4 star mexican food!!!
Nice little place for quick tacos or drinks.
The food is great, Taco Tuesday is awesome! On Fridays they have a great DJ.
Great spot for a unique taco experience.
Avocado tacos and the salsa bar are what keep bringing me back. Friendly and knowledgeable staff make the experience great. Plus, it just looks awesome in there.
Great spicy chicken tacos, the chips and salsa were also good. Free refills on the chips and salsa as well!
Decent tacos. Great vibes. Cool space. Bar in the middle. Small patio. Pretty good option for tacos for the area.
Decent tacos but the $3 tacos are good
Great fish battered tacos and amust is the appetizers called corn fundido!

Decided to come here after doing a search for dog friendly restaurants. I was not disappointed. Everything is made in house so it's fresh. Their brunch menu is pretty tasty. I had the Steak and Egg skillet. It contained steak and eggs, as well as potatoes, avocado's, onions, and salsa. The churro donut was sweet and delicious. I recommend giving this place a visit!
Not authentic Mexican food but definitely authentic ingredients which are configured into a deliciously unauthentic taco :D

Tacos and service were excellent.

Once again I think the owner of this company should really change the menu. The plates were extremely DIRTY. My mothers friend sugar cane stick was EXTREMELY DRY.
I like the way it tastes.
Decent taco, salsa bar is a plus. Somewhat pricey and not as authentic as it could be, but it's what you get in River North.

Maybe I was expecting too much based on the reviews and I've had great street tacos and these were just as good but the service is kind of weird. Super disappointed in the tacos. I tried three different kinds and all three were not up to par and were a bit on the soggy side.
An awesome selection of tacos and Mexican food. Love their lunchtime specials
A dress code ? Proper... shoes? For tacos? F THAT. So ridiculous. shall never return.
<3 Tacos, Local crafts to choose from and and fun atmosphere!
Awesome tacos in the city
amazing tacos - their smoked brisket is as good as some of the places in the city who only serve that.

The Al Pastor is unbelievable.  The tortillas were handmade , there was a pleasant sweetness that was not overly cloying and the pork was tender and juicy.  The brisket taco and carnitas were also was delicious.  The posole makes you want to see the team of Mexican grandmothers making it and the Michelada is housemade as well.  They seem to do everything from scratch here and it really makes the experience worthwhile.
It's a little expensive and there are much better tacos to be had in Chicago.
Really good tacos, nice atmosphere, quick service and pretty reasonable
Great spot for tacos. My co workers and I have lunch here and we really enjoy the food, fast service, friendly staff and the nice environment.
Good tacos. Hard to get full on a reasonable budget though.
The ceviche was pretty good.

Wanted a quick meal because it was late. Service was good. Food came out hot, tasty, and quick. Loved the special, chicken enchilada! The grilled salmon taco was good. The salsa with the chips and salsa is not a traditional tomato salsa. It has a deeper flavor versus a fresh tomato salsa.
Tacos are good, but expensive.
No draft beer ?
Cheap fast delicious tacos. Great for groups since you pay first. Orders can get mixed up but food usually comes out very quickly
Al pastor and brisket tacos were great. Outstanding beer selection.
Loved my tacos! Will do again 10/10
Not bad but not the best tacos
Mike D was here!
I can believe how good the food is here.

Tallboy Taco is basically the front bar of Nacional 27. While Nacional 27 is an upscale-ish restaurant, Tallboy Taco has a wider appeal, and is appropriate for a quick lunch or takeout. Try their agua frescas - I loved the lemon chia variety.

The food was great and very quick to get seated. However, the tables were super small to fit tacos, drinks, and all the other items. We waited longer to get a waiter at the table than it took us to get our food.

The service and the chips & salsa were excellent. The tacos had good flavors, but they mostly came from the sauces/toppings, not the meat. The margarita prices were steep and the beer menu was not very large or diverse.

I could sit at Tallboy Taco all day and eat their homemade tortilla chips. They are so great. Definitely not what I would normally ever recommend, but the kale salad is delicious! Just give it a try, you'll see what I mean!
Right where Nacional 27 is, this place has GREAT tacos. Good happy hour specials. Large establishment. Dancing on certain nights. Reasonably priced. One of my favorites.
Pretty good! River north prices for tacos but well worth it on the company card :)
Classic taco spot for Chicago. Doesn't touch some of the big names like Big Star though. Still a good spot to check out once.

Loved their food!  Those tacos were too good!  I love little tacos - they allow me to eat more than I should, but convince myself that because they are small I am still doing okay.  All I can say is give me more more more!

Loved the al pastor taco- highly recommend it. Also, if you like your guacamole with a kick, then definitely check out their hot guac! All of their desserts were delish and worth trying. I would be very likely to bring my taco loving friends back.
Tallboy Taco was amazing!  Make sure to try the flavor filler pastor and brisket with pickled onion and cilantro!!!!  So GREAT!

All of their tacos are amazing.  That said, make sure you keep some room in your tummy for that tres leches dessert....INSANE.  I had it with a mango cream sauce but ask for the chocolate and caramel served with the churros.  Thank me later!

Neighborhood gem! Tallboy Taco serves the best beer-battered fish tacos (tilapia) I've ever had. We also ordered the cheese fundido and the guacamole for the group and it was perfect for sharing. Found my new taco spot!
